If you can, deliver it to FreeGeek. They'll re-use or refurbish it,
and if it's completely unusable they'll take it apart and get a few
semoleans from their upstream recycler.

http://freegeektoronto.org/donate/

Better them than a for-profit recycler.

- --Bob.


